tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal odor) may indicate urinary tract pathology. Marked ketonuria is present without hyperglycemia, and HbA1c is low, possibly reflecting anemia or recent hypoglycemia. Electrolytes and other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and possible urinary tract infection or other renal pathology.
